##########    MC Nutr
df <- read.csv("menu.csv", check.names = FALSE)
df <- df %>% select(Category, Item, `Serving Size`, Calories, `Total Fat`, `Saturated Fat`, 
                    Sodium, Carbohydrates, `Dietary Fiber`, Protein, Sugars, `Vitamin A (% Daily Value)`, 
                    `Vitamin C (% Daily Value)`, `Calcium (% Daily Value)`, `Iron (% Daily Value)`)

######Change the some % in the data to mg. Time these percentage with the serving mg

#Get the Daily mg value needed by human adult from internet, trans them into mg
cols <- c('Vitamin A (% Daily Value)', 'Vitamin C (% Daily Value)', 'Calcium (% Daily Value)', 'Iron (% Daily Value)')
df['Vitamin A (% Daily Value)'] <- df['Vitamin A (% Daily Value)']*900*0.01
df['Vitamin C (% Daily Value)'] <- df['Vitamin C (% Daily Value)']*90*0.01
df['Calcium (% Daily Value)'] <- df['Calcium (% Daily Value)']*1300*0.01
df['Iron (% Daily Value)'] <- df['Iron (% Daily Value)']*18*0.01
#######Change name of % to mg

MC <- df %>% rename_with(~str_replace(., " \\(% Daily Value\\)", ""), cols)

cat <- MC %>%
  select(Category) %>%
  group_by(Category) %>%
  mutate(count = n())

cat <- distinct(cat)

cat <- cat[order(cat$count, decreasing = TRUE), ]  # 按照计数从大到小排序

colors <- brewer_pal(palette = "Set2")(nrow(cat))  # 使用Set2调色板生成颜色
## Warning in RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(n, pal): n too large, allowed maximum for palette Set2 is 8
## Returning the palette you asked for with that many colors
plot_cat <- ggplot(data = cat, aes(x = reorder(Category, -count), y = count, fill = Category)) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
  theme_classic() +
  geom_text(aes(label = count), color = "black", size = 5) +
  scale_x_discrete(guide = guide_axis(angle = 45)) +
  ggtitle("McDonald's Menu by Category")

plot_cat

cal <- MC %>%
  select(Category, Item, Calories) %>%
  group_by(Category) %>%
  summarise(median_Protein = median(Calories))  # 计算中位数

cal <- cal[order(cal$median_Protein), ]  # 按照中位数排序

MC$Category <- factor(MC$Category, levels = cal$Category)  # 设置正确的顺序

p_cal <- ggplot(data = MC, aes(x = Category, y = Calories, fill = Category)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_classic() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  ggtitle("McDonald's Carbohydrates per Category") +
  scale_x_discrete(guide = guide_axis(angle = 45))

p_cal

Total_Fat <- MC %>%
  select(Category, Item, `Total Fat`) %>%
  group_by(Category) %>%
  summarise(median_Total_Fat = median(`Total Fat`))  # 计算中位数

Total_Fat <- Total_Fat[order(Total_Fat$median_Total_Fat), ]  # 按照中位数排序

MC$Category <- factor(MC$Category, levels = Total_Fat$Category)  # 设置正确的顺序

p_Total_Fat <- ggplot(data = MC, aes(x = Category, y = `Total Fat`, fill = Category)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_classic() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  ggtitle("McDonald's Total Fat per Category") +
